						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script of the 16th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Yuda ben Shelomoh de Bolognese</name>: inscribed in the colophon, folio 214r.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Fra Gir. Durazzano</name>, active in 1640-41 in <name type="place">Modena-Reggio</name>: inscribed with his name, 1640? (folio 214r); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">89</ref>.</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Renato da Modena</name>: inscribed with his name, 'Visto per mi fr. Renato da Mod., 1626' (folio 214r); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">132-133</ref>.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Luigi da Bologna</name>: inscribed with his name: 'Visto per mi fra Luigi del 1600' (folio 214v); a converted Jew working for the Inquisition as censor (active 1590-1609), see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">104</ref>, and appendix § 112-117. </p>
						</additions>
